cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

The paper deals with 3D shape reconstruction from a single image using a deep neural network. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for image processing and graphics (cs.GR) for 3D shape representation. The use of a neural network for mapping an image to a vector of network weights involves machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) techniques. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of a deep neural network for shape classification, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE).
